item.description:
**Get new JWT token using refresh token**

### ✅ What Happens
Exchanges valid refresh token for new JWT access token. Extends user session without re-authenticating. Refresh token stored in RefreshToken collection with user reference.

### 📝 REQUEST BODY
```json
{
  "refreshToken": "507f1f77bcf86cd799439012" // ✓ Required, from initial login
}
```

### 📤 SUCCESS RESPONSE (200 OK)
```json
{
  "status": "success",
  "data": {
    "token": "eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9..."
  }
}
```

### ❌ ERROR RESPONSES
- **401 Unauthorized**: Refresh token invalid/expired/not found

**Authenticate via OAuth provider (Google, GitHub, Facebook)**

### ✅ What Happens
Verifies OAuth token with provider. Creates user if first-time login, logs in if exists. Returns JWT token. Provider verified using oauthVerifiers utilities.

### 📝 REQUEST BODY
```json
{
  "provider": "google",    // ✓ Required: "google" | "github" | "facebook"
  "idToken": "eyJh..."      // ✓ Required: Valid token from OAuth provider
}
```

### 📤 SUCCESS RESPONSE (200 OK)
```json
{
  "status": "success",
  "data": {
    "user": {
      "_id": "507f1f77bcf86cd799439011",
      "name": "Sarah Johnson",
      "email": "sarah@gmail.com",
      "oauthProvider": "google",
      "photo": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/..."
    },
    "token": "eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9..."
  }
}
```

**Change user password**

### 🔐 Authentication Required
Bearer token

### ✅ What Happens
Verifies current password, validates new password strength, hashes with bcrypt, updates in database.

### 📝 REQUEST BODY
```json
{
  "passwordCurrent": "SecurePass123!",  // ✓ Required
  "password": "NewSecurePass456!",      // ✓ Required, min 8, uppercase, number, special
  "passwordConfirm": "NewSecurePass456!" // ✓ Required, must match password
}
```

### 📤 SUCCESS RESPONSE (200 OK)
```json
{
  "status": "success",
  "data": {
    "user": {
      "_id": "507f1f77bcf86cd799439011",
      "email": "sarah.johnson@example.com"
    }
  }
}
```

